	<div class="article">
		<div class="section">
			<p class="extra-space">A long-standing and well-renowned asset management company, Lazard was looking to update their old website. With more than 43 offices in over 40 countries, their business was complex and unfortunately that showed through their site. A maze of product offerings, complex content permissioning, and disparate regional sites, users had a difficult time navigating and finding the information they needed.</p> 
			<p>I was the lead UX designer on the project and helped organize their content, streamline their navigation, and create a flexible design system that would scale across multiple devices and multiple country sites.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="section">
			<div class="image-wrapper"><img src="images/lam-homepage.png"></div>
